  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "Cone of Silence",
    "overview_subtitle": "Volume of a Cone",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students conduct an experiment and conclude that it takes three times a cone’s content to fill a cylinder with the same dimensions. They use a pyramid’s volume formula to derive a cone’s volume formula. Students use the formula to calculate the volume, height, or radius of a cone. They apply the volume of a cone to solve real-world problems."
  },
