    {
      "overview_item_type": "essential_ideas",
      "overview_item_content_type": "html",
      "overview_item_title": "Essential Ideas",
      "overview_item_data": {
        "overview_item_data_type": "list",
        "overview_item_data_items": [
          "A cone is a three-dimensional object with a circular or oval base and one vertex.",
          "The formula for a cone’s volume is <math><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>B</mi><mi>h</mi></math>, where <math><mi>V</mi></math> is the volume, <math><mi>B</mi></math> is the area of the base, and <math><mi>h</mi></math> is the height.",
          "You can write the formula for a cone’s volume as <math><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math>, where <math><mi>V</mi></math> is the volume, <math><mi>r</mi></math> is the length of the radius of the base, and <math><mi>h</mi></math> is the height.",
          "You can use the Pythagorean Theorem to determine a cone’s height when given the length of the radius and slant height."
        ]
      }
    },
